JSPs may be corrupted when renaming packages, for example:

In a dynamic web project I have the following Java files:

  package root.one;
  public interface Electrical {}

  package root.two;
  import root.one.Electrical;
  public class ElectricLightBulb implements Electrical {};

I now create a JSP:

  <%@page import="root.one.Electrical"%>
  <%@page import="root.two.ElectricLightBulb"%>
  <%
  Electrical product = new ElectricLightBulb();
  %>

If I now rename root to electric_shop (choosing also to rename subpackages) then my JSP becomes corrupt:

  <%@page import="electric_shop.one.Electricalage import="electric_shop.two.ElectricLightBulbElectrical product = new ElectricLightBulb();
  %>

I have seen this in Eclipse 3.2.0, 3.2.1 (Webtools 1.5.2).
